<item>
            <title>[LU-3236] After DNE upgrade from 1.8.9 to 2.4, failure on test suite sanity test_228b: Fail to start MDT</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3236</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for sarah &amp;lt;sarah@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;http://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/2f8d6cf2-add9-11e2-b72d-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/2f8d6cf2-add9-11e2-b72d-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test test_228b failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fail to start MDT.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;MDS 1 console&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Lustre: DEBUG MARKER: == sanity test 228b: idle OI blocks can be reused after MDT restart == 11:36:02 (1366914962)
LustreError: 161-6: The target named lustre-MDT0000 is already running. Double-mount may have compromised the disk journal.
LustreError: 19049:0:(obd_mount.c:1264:lustre_fill_super()) Unable to mount  (-114)
Lustre: DEBUG MARKER: sanity test_228b: @@@@@@ FAIL: Fail to start MDT.
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
